{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":960,"text":"When Dorothy was a little girl,"},{"time":2560,"text":"she was fascinated by her goldfish."},{"time":5080,"text":"Her father explained to her that fish swim\nby quickly wagging their tails"},{"time":8560,"text":"to propel themselves through the water."},{"time":11040,"text":"Without hesitation,\nlittle Dorothy responded,"},{"time":13200,"text":"\"Yes, Daddy, and fish swim backwards\nby wagging their heads.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":16480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":18120,"text":"In her mind, it was a fact\nas true as any other."},{"time":20960,"text":"Fish swim backwards\nby wagging their heads."},{"time":23320,"text":"She believed it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25320,"text":"Our lives are full\nof fish swimming backwards."},{"time":28320,"text":"We make assumptions\nand faulty leaps of logic."},{"time":30840,"text":"We harbor bias."},{"time":32119,"text":"We know that we are right,\nand they are wrong."},{"time":34400,"text":"We fear the worst."},{"time":36040,"text":"We strive for unattainable perfection."},{"time":38920,"text":"We tell ourselves\nwhat we can and cannot do."},{"time":41880,"text":"In our minds, fish swim by in reverse\nfrantically wagging their heads"},{"time":46000,"text":"and we don't even notice them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49160,"text":"I'm going to tell you\nfive facts about myself."},{"time":51360,"text":"One fact is not true."},{"time":53760,"text":"One: I graduated from Harvard at 19\nwith an honors degree in mathematics."},{"time":59680,"text":"Two: I currently run\na construction company in Orlando."},{"time":64920,"text":"Three: I starred on a television sitcom."},{"time":69440,"text":"Four: I lost my sight\nto a rare genetic eye disease."},{"time":74960,"text":"Five: I served as a law clerk\nto two US Supreme Court justices."},{"time":80360,"text":"Which fact is not true?"},{"time":83880,"text":"Actually, they're all true."},{"time":86240,"text":"Yeah. They're all true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88800,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":92680,"text":"At this point, most people really\nonly care about the television show."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":99680,"text":"I know this from experience."},{"time":102320,"text":"OK, so the show was NBC's\n\"Saved by the Bell: The New Class.\""},{"time":105680,"text":"And I played Weasel Wyzell,"},{"time":110240,"text":"who was the sort of dorky,\nnerdy character on the show,"},{"time":114320,"text":"which made it a very\nmajor acting challenge"},{"time":119120,"text":"for me as a 13-year-old boy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":123320,"text":"Now, did you struggle\nwith number four, my blindness?"},{"time":127120,"text":"Why is that?"},{"time":129280,"text":"We make assumptions\nabout so-called disabilities."},{"time":132280,"text":"As a blind man, I confront\nothers' incorrect assumptions"},{"time":135480,"text":"about my abilities every day."},{"time":138640,"text":"My point today is not\nabout my blindness, however."},{"time":141200,"text":"It's about my vision."},{"time":143480,"text":"Going blind taught me\nto live my life eyes wide open."},{"time":148200,"text":"It taught me to spot\nthose backwards-swimming fish"},{"time":150600,"text":"that our minds create."},{"time":152120,"text":"Going blind cast them into focus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155760,"text":"What does it feel like to see?"},{"time":158720,"text":"It's immediate and passive."},{"time":160800,"text":"You open your eyes and there's the world."},{"time":162960,"text":"Seeing is believing. Sight is truth."},{"time":165080,"text":"Right?"},{"time":167120,"text":"Well, that's what I thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169520,"text":"Then, from age 12 to 25,\nmy retinas progressively deteriorated."},{"time":175280,"text":"My sight became an increasingly bizarre"},{"time":178320,"text":"carnival funhouse hall\nof mirrors and illusions."},{"time":181640,"text":"The salesperson I was relieved\nto spot in a store"},{"time":184000,"text":"was really a mannequin."},{"time":185880,"text":"Reaching down to wash my hands,"},{"time":187400,"text":"I suddenly saw it was\na urinal I was touching, not a sink,"},{"time":190640,"text":"when my fingers felt its true shape."},{"time":193160,"text":"A friend described\nthe photograph in my hand,"},{"time":195320,"text":"and only then I could see\nthe image depicted."},{"time":198720,"text":"Objects appeared, morphed\nand disappeared in my reality."},{"time":204080,"text":"It was difficult and exhausting to see."},{"time":207600,"text":"I pieced together fragmented,\ntransitory images,"},{"time":210880,"text":"consciously analyzed the clues,"},{"time":212880,"text":"searched for some logic\nin my crumbling kaleidoscope,"},{"time":216840,"text":"until I saw nothing at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219600,"text":"I learned that what we see"},{"time":221280,"text":"is not universal truth."},{"time":224200,"text":"It is not objective reality."},{"time":228000,"text":"What we see is a unique,\npersonal, virtual reality"},{"time":232720,"text":"that is masterfully\nconstructed by our brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235560,"text":"Let me explain with a bit\nof amateur neuroscience."},{"time":237918,"text":"Your visual cortex takes up\nabout 30 percent of your brain."},{"time":241560,"text":"That's compared to approximately\neight percent for touch"},{"time":245040,"text":"and two to three percent for hearing."},{"time":247600,"text":"Every second, your eyes\ncan send your visual cortex"},{"time":251360,"text":"as many as two billion\npieces of information."},{"time":254360,"text":"The rest of your body can send your brain\nonly an additional billion."},{"time":258680,"text":"So sight is one third\nof your brain by volume"},{"time":262920,"text":"and can claim about two thirds\nof your brain's processing resources."},{"time":267040,"text":"It's no surprise then"},{"time":268280,"text":"that the illusion\nof sight is so compelling."},{"time":270400,"text":"But make no mistake about it:\nsight is an illusion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273920,"text":"Here's where it gets interesting."},{"time":275760,"text":"To create the experience of sight,"},{"time":277880,"text":"your brain references your conceptual\nunderstanding of the world,"},{"time":281440,"text":"other knowledge, your memories,\nopinions, emotions, mental attention."},{"time":285520,"text":"All of these things and far more\nare linked in your brain to your sight."},{"time":291040,"text":"These linkages work both ways,\nand usually occur subconsciously."},{"time":294480,"text":"So for example,"},{"time":296360,"text":"what you see impacts how you feel,"},{"time":298520,"text":"and the way you feel\ncan literally change what you see."},{"time":302040,"text":"Numerous studies demonstrate this."},{"time":304600,"text":"If you are asked to estimate"},{"time":306480,"text":"the walking speed of a man\nin a video, for example,"},{"time":309680,"text":"your answer will be different if you're\ntold to think about cheetahs or turtles."},{"time":315120,"text":"A hill appears steeper\nif you've just exercised,"},{"time":318440,"text":"and a landmark appears farther away"},{"time":320680,"text":"if you're wearing a heavy backpack."},{"time":323960,"text":"We have arrived\nat a fundamental contradiction."},{"time":328160,"text":"What you see is a complex\nmental construction of your own making,"},{"time":332600,"text":"but you experience it passively"},{"time":334400,"text":"as a direct representation\nof the world around you."},{"time":337680,"text":"You create your own reality,\nand you believe it."},{"time":341560,"text":"I believed mine until it broke apart."},{"time":344920,"text":"The deterioration of my eyes\nshattered the illusion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348720,"text":"You see, sight is just one way"},{"time":351040,"text":"we shape our reality."},{"time":353280,"text":"We create our own realities\nin many other ways."},{"time":357160,"text":"Let's take fear as just one example."},{"time":361440,"text":"Your fears distort your reality."},{"time":365880,"text":"Under the warped logic of fear,\nanything is better than the uncertain."},{"time":370080,"text":"Fear fills the void at all costs,"},{"time":372560,"text":"passing off what you dread\nfor what you know,"},{"time":374720,"text":"offering up the worst\nin place of the ambiguous,"},{"time":377520,"text":"substituting assumption for reason."},{"time":380120,"text":"Psychologists have\na great term for it: awfulizing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":384000,"text":"Right?"},{"time":385560,"text":"Fear replaces the unknown with the awful."},{"time":390080,"text":"Now, fear is self-realizing."},{"time":392000,"text":"When you face the greatest need"},{"time":393760,"text":"to look outside yourself\nand think critically,"},{"time":396440,"text":"fear beats a retreat\ndeep inside your mind,"},{"time":399280,"text":"shrinking and distorting your view,"},{"time":401080,"text":"drowning your capacity\nfor critical thought"},{"time":403160,"text":"with a flood of disruptive emotions."},{"time":405880,"text":"When you face a compelling\nopportunity to take action,"},{"time":408760,"text":"fear lulls you into inaction,"},{"time":411280,"text":"enticing you to passively watch\nits prophecies fulfill themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417880,"text":"When I was diagnosed\nwith my blinding disease,"},{"time":420120,"text":"I knew blindness would ruin my life."},{"time":424400,"text":"Blindness was a death sentence\nfor my independence."},{"time":427360,"text":"It was the end of achievement for me."},{"time":430600,"text":"Blindness meant I would live\nan unremarkable life,"},{"time":434600,"text":"small and sad,"},{"time":436320,"text":"and likely alone."},{"time":438280,"text":"I knew it."},{"time":441440,"text":"This was a fiction born of my fears,\nbut I believed it."},{"time":444800,"text":"It was a lie, but it was my reality,"},{"time":447440,"text":"just like those backwards-swimming fish\nin little Dorothy's mind."},{"time":451920,"text":"If I had not confronted\nthe reality of my fear,"},{"time":454440,"text":"I would have lived it."},{"time":456200,"text":"I am certain of that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459920,"text":"So how do you live your life\neyes wide open?"},{"time":463480,"text":"It is a learned discipline."},{"time":465520,"text":"It can be taught. It can be practiced."},{"time":468680,"text":"I will summarize very briefly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471640,"text":"Hold yourself accountable"},{"time":473560,"text":"for every moment, every thought,"},{"time":476080,"text":"every detail."},{"time":478120,"text":"See beyond your fears."},{"time":479800,"text":"Recognize your assumptions."},{"time":481560,"text":"Harness your internal strength."},{"time":483360,"text":"Silence your internal critic."},{"time":485560,"text":"Correct your misconceptions\nabout luck and about success."},{"time":489480,"text":"Accept your strengths and your weaknesses,\nand understand the difference."},{"time":493600,"text":"Open your hearts"},{"time":494920,"text":"to your bountiful blessings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497480,"text":"Your fears, your critics,"},{"time":499720,"text":"your heroes, your villains --"},{"time":501600,"text":"they are your excuses,"},{"time":504640,"text":"rationalizations, shortcuts,"},{"time":507000,"text":"justifications, your surrender."},{"time":510360,"text":"They are fictions you perceive as reality."},{"time":514000,"text":"Choose to see through them."},{"time":515679,"text":"Choose to let them go."},{"time":518080,"text":"You are the creator of your reality."},{"time":522240,"text":"With that empowerment\ncomes complete responsibility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526440,"text":"I chose to step out of fear's tunnel\ninto terrain uncharted and undefined."},{"time":532440,"text":"I chose to build there a blessed life."},{"time":536120,"text":"Far from alone,"},{"time":537920,"text":"I share my beautiful life with Dorothy,"},{"time":540920,"text":"my beautiful wife,"},{"time":542600,"text":"with our triplets,\nwhom we call the Tripskys,"},{"time":546400,"text":"and with the latest addition\nto the family,"},{"time":548440,"text":"sweet baby Clementine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550840,"text":"What do you fear?"},{"time":553600,"text":"What lies do you tell yourself?"},{"time":556520,"text":"How do you embellish your truth\nand write your own fictions?"},{"time":560360,"text":"What reality are you\ncreating for yourself?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":564200,"text":"In your career and personal life,\nin your relationships,"},{"time":567400,"text":"and in your heart and soul,"},{"time":569040,"text":"your backwards-swimming fish\ndo you great harm."},{"time":572560,"text":"They exact a toll in missed opportunities\nand unrealized potential,"},{"time":577400,"text":"and they engender insecurity and distrust"},{"time":579800,"text":"where you seek fulfillment and connection."},{"time":583560,"text":"I urge you to search them out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587360,"text":"Helen Keller said that the only thing\nworse than being blind"},{"time":591560,"text":"is having sight but no vision."},{"time":594920,"text":"For me, going blind\nwas a profound blessing,"},{"time":598720,"text":"because blindness gave me vision."},{"time":601720,"text":"I hope you can see what I see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604280,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605520,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":620720,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Isaac, before you\nleave the stage, just a question."},{"time":623920,"text":"This is an audience of entrepreneurs,\nof doers, of innovators."},{"time":627720,"text":"You are a CEO of a company\ndown in Florida,"},{"time":631400,"text":"and many are probably wondering,"},{"time":633560,"text":"how is it to be a blind CEO?"},{"time":635800,"text":"What kind of specific challenges\ndo you have, and how do you overcome them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":639600,"text":"Isaac Lidsky: Well,\nthe biggest challenge became a blessing."},{"time":642760,"text":"I don't get visual feedback from people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":648000,"text":"BG: What's that noise there? IL: Yeah."},{"time":650200,"text":"So, for example,\nin my leadership team meetings,"},{"time":653720,"text":"I don't see facial\nexpressions or gestures."},{"time":657640,"text":"I've learned to solicit\na lot more verbal feedback."},{"time":661400,"text":"I basically force people\nto tell me what they think."},{"time":666080,"text":"And in this respect,"},{"time":667960,"text":"it's become, like I said, a real blessing\nfor me personally and for my company,"},{"time":672080,"text":"because we communicate\nat a far deeper level,"},{"time":675400,"text":"we avoid ambiguities,"},{"time":678080,"text":"and most important, my team knows\nthat what they think truly matters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686560,"text":"BG: Isaac, thank you for coming to TED.\nIL: Thank you, Bruno."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689480,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}